1. e4 c5 2. d4
{ Playing immediately for the center, but even here White cannot expect an advantage from the opening. }
2... cxd4 3. Qxd4 { Taking with the queen leads to losing some tempi. } 3...
Nc6 4. Qd2 Nf6 5. Nc3 e6
{ As we will see in the 2. Nc3 lines, if Black has already played ...d6 this position is playable for White, but here Black can play 5...g6 or the simplest 5...e6 followed by ...d5 and Black has no problems. }
