{ This is the continuation for which it was believed that this line could lead to White's advantage. }
6... Nxd5 { The simplest. } 7. Ne5 Bd7 8. Bxc6 Bxc6
{ If White's pawn was still on f2, White castles to take advantage of Black's ruined pawn structure after  9.Nxc6  . But the bad position of the f-pawn changes the evaluation of the position. }
9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. O-O Be7 { Black is perfectly fine. } *

