6... Nf6 7. h3 O-O 8. Qd2 Rb8
{ The plan with Black is simple: just push the pawns to the queenside. } 9.
Nge2
{ If  9.f4  then  9...Nd7  , We already know this maneuver and know that we cannot play  9...b5  right away. }
9... b5 10. f4 b4 11. Nd1 Nd7 { Preventing e5. } 12. O-O Nd4 13. g4 a5 14. Ng3
