2... d6 { 2...d6 is not very logical. } 3. d4 { White occupies the center. }
3... Nf6 4. Bd3
{ This is Black's main problem, although  4.f3  is a very decent move too.   Black's idea is revealed after  4.dxc5  Nc6!  5.cxd6  Nxe4  when White loses the d6-pawn.  Black has a good game.   @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pp2pppp/2np1n2/2P5/4P3/2P5/PP3PPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 1 5@@EndFEN@@  5.f3  d5  is unclear. }
4... g6 5. h3 { 5.dxc5  d5  could be OK for Black. } 5... Bg7 6. Nf3 O-O 7. O-O
Qc7 8. Re1
{ Black has a playable position but at the same time, it's obvious that he hasn't fully equalized. }
