{ White doesn't have the option of playing Nc3 now, unlike in the Scandinavian Defense. }
4. Nf3 { 4.d4  Nf6  5.Nf3  transposes to the text move. } 4... Nf6 5. d4
{ 5.Na3  is not a logical move. White certainly needs to play d2-d4 whereas the knight can remain flexible for now. }
5... Bg4
{ This used to be Kasparov's go-to defense against the Alapin Variation. It was a respected variation when he was still an active player, but nowadays, it's unclear if Black can actually equalize following 5...Bg4. }
6. Nbd2
{ I introduced this novelty in a game against Kasparov, in Moscow in 1995. It poses Black serious problems. }
6... e6 7. Qa4+ Nbd7 8. Bc4 Qd6
{ Black finishes development rather effortlessly. } *

