10. Bxe6 Qxe6 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Qxd4 Rd8 { This position is just equal. } 13.
Qh4 { Black has no problems after  13.Qb4  Qc6=  either. } 13... Qe2
{ This move kills White's hope of getting an opening advantage. White must take measures against the threat of ...Rd1 and Black completes development with ...e6 and ...Be7 @@StartBracket@@attacking the queen on h4@@EndBracket@@ while White's development is hampered.   13...h5  , aiming for ...Qg4, is also a good move. }
