{ This is White's best try. Generally speaking, Re1 is a more useful move than Qe2.   12.Ng5  is pointless after  12...Bd5=  . }
12... cxb3 { This move makes achieving d2-d4 too easy for White. } 13. axb3 O-O
14. d4 Bd5 15. h4
{ White has some initiative on the kingside and firmly controls the center.   After the immediate  15...e5  , Black's pieces are loose after  16.Nxe5  Nxe5  17.dxe5  Bxe5  18.Nb5  . White's opening was certainly a success after  18...Qb8  19.Nd4  . }
