1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
{ The most dangerous move that White can try against the Sicilian. This move prepares d4 to fight for the center. }
2... b6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Bb7
{ Black has reached a bad version of any Sicilian here. The reason is that the typical queenside expansion a6-b5 is harder to achieve due to the already wasted tempo b7-b6. }
5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e6 7. f3
{ Black will have to play ...b5 anyway in the future, so he is a tempo down compared to the good versions of the Sicilian Defense. Qd2 next is in the menu. }
