{ The most dangerous move that White can try. This move prepares d4 to fight for the center. }
2... e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6
{ The Paulsen. Black is trying to expand on the queenside with ...b5 and ...Bb7 or playing the flexible ...Qc7.Besides, Black can go back to other 2...e6 Sicilian setups as well. This is a very playable system that has been played by strong Grandmasters like Caruana, Svidler, and more. White has two dangerous configurations against the Paulse. Let's have a look at them separately. }
5. Bd3
{ The idea is to play c4 next, gaining space. restricting ...b5 from Black. } *

