3. Nc3
{ This is one of the ways that White has to avoid the Sveshnikov and look for advantage far away from it. It became very popular 15 years ago. }
3... e5
{ This is the radical way of playing. It stops d4 forever at the cost of weakening the d6 and d5-squares. }
4. Bc4 d6 5. d3
{ I have played many games with both colors with this position, and also other strong players did. This system reminds me of a Ruy Lopez more than a Sicilian. Black is quite solid. There are good chances to equalize, but White has his triumphs to avoid his opponent to do so. }
