[Black "Summary"]
[Result "*"]

{ There are quite a lot of playable sidelines for White after 2.Nf3 e6 but they're not so dangerous if you know how to meet them.  For White, I recommend including one or two of them in your arsenal - perhaps 3.g3 or 3.b3 for Rapid or Blitz.   3.c3 is perhaps the most straightforward and risk-free way to minimize theory and just get a pleasant opening position. Even if they're not objectively the best, if Black is not well-prepared, it can lead to an easy advantage.  For Black, having seen this lesson, you shouldn't experience any difficulties equalizing against those sidelines. }
