7. Bc4
{ Again, the only way to really challenge Black. White is still trying to build up the ideal setup connected to castling queenside. }
7... O-O 8. O-O Nxe4
{ This works well, which is why White usually plays @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/pp1pppbp/2n2np1/8/2BNP3/2N1B3/PPP2PPP/R2QK2R w KQ - 5 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Bb3  . It should be mentioned that @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/pp1pppbp/2n2np1/8/2BNP3/2N1B3/PPP2PPP/R2Q1RK1 b - - 6 8@@EndFEN@@  8...d6  is also fine already, given White has castled kingside. }
*

