{ 11...b6  is already not the same anymore, as White can castle queenside. }
12. Nxb5 Qxd5 13. Qxd5 Nxd5
{ White is still a pawn-up and would be much better if given a few moves to consolidate. It seems it's hard to achieve complete consolidation though, as practice has shown. Boris Gelfand drew both his games against MVL and Giri from this position. }
