8... d6
{ From all the moves we have seen so far this is obviously the most natural. }
9. h3
{ This was played by Anand in Linares against Kasparov, but shouldn't pose many problems. }
9... Na5
{ Even better now, compared to @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/pp1pppbp/2n2np1/8/3NP3/1BN1B3/PPP2PPP/R2QK2R b KQ - 6 8@@EndFEN@@  8...Re8  ,  since it's much more useful to have the pawn on d6. }
10. O-O b6 11. Re1 Bb7
{ Attacking the pawn on e4, forcing the bishop away from e3. } 12. Bg5 Nxb3 13.
axb3 h6
{ It's important to prevent White from exchanging bishops with Qd1-d2 and Bg5-h6. }
14. Bh4 Qd7 { Black is perfectly fine. } *

