11. Re1 Rfe8
{ It is definitely interesting to study this position further, as it can be played with either color. I personally wouldn't mind playing it with Black, since the position is hard to crack, but I can also see the appeal for White.  Note that the only reason White is fighting for an advantage is the fact that the queen is on a5. In these types of positions, where the queen is usually on d8, the move ...Nc6-a5 is a typical idea to liquidate the strong bishop on b3. The fact that this operation is not available here makes it slightly more playable for White. }
