5... Nf6
{ This is another unusual and inferior way to play for Black, doing everything they can to target the e-pawn. }
6. Nc3 Bb4 7. Nb5
{ Counterattacking on the dark-squares and if allowed, Nd6+ will lead to an overwhelming positional advantage for White. }
