[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Lesson 34: 2.Nf3 e6 Main lines"]
[Black "2...e6 Main lines: 4...Nf6 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6
{ In this chapter we will analyze the mainlines of the 2...e6 Sicilian starting with the immediate  3.d4  cxd4  4.Nxd4  . This is the most critical approach for White and should be taken very seriously. }
3. d4 { Opening the center immediately. } 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
{ This is another option that will be useful for the White player to know how to meet. }
5. Nc3
{ Threatening e5, embarrassing the knight.  5.e5  is impossible due to  5...Qa5+  dropping the pawn with check. }
5... Bb4
{ This is a tricky old line that was supposed to be not so clear, but these days it's basically engine-refuted.  5...Nc6  is an option, which will transpose to the 2...Nc6 move order, which we've examinedhere. }
6. e5 { The critical response, deflecting the knight so we can play Qg4. } 6...
Nd5 { Forced. } 7. Qg4
{ Maybe the strongest move, reverting to the sharp knockout lines.  7.Bd2  is also very good, and if such a simple move works, there should be no point in playing this way for Black.  7...Nxc3  8.bxc3  Be7   8...Bf8  at least stops Qg4 but simple development  9.Bd3  followed by O-O offers White great development advantage in exchange for the bad structure. White is better.  9.Qg4  hitting the g-pawn is very annoying. }
7... g6
{ This is a poor, weakening move.  7...Nxc3  as we've seen, is very bad for Black...  8.Qxg7  Rf8  9.a3  Nb5+  10.axb4  Nxd4  11.Bh6  Qe7  12.Bd3  and White wins an easy game. }
8. Nb5
{ This is perhaps the strongest move, going in for the kill on the dark-squares.  8.Bd2  is also good. }
8... Nc6 9. Qg3 { Simply defending the center. } 9... O-O
{ Where else was the king going? } 10. a3
{ Asking the defender of all those dark squares what it's intentions are. }
10... Be7
{ There's really no option to take on c3, and permanently cede the battle for the dark-squares. }
11. Bh6 Bh4 12. Qh3
{ This is a pretty miserable position for Black, even if they're not getting mated right away. }
