{ With the idea of ...Qb4. } 12. Bc4 O-O 13. Bb3 d5
{ Black is forced to go to some pretty extreme measures to stop White's kingside attack. }
14. exd5 Rxb3 15. cxb3 cxd5 16. Nxd5
{ Cannot be played for tactical reasons. a2 is too much of a liability. } 16...
Nxd5 17. Qxd5 Qxa2 { ...Bxf5 and ...Rc8+ is the big threat. } 18. g4 Bxf5
{ Funnily, g4 doesn't stop ... Bxf5. } 19. gxf5 Rc8+ 20. Kd2 Rd8
{ Black is of course winning here. } *

