{ The idea of this move is to prevent Black from playing b4. The reason is that the a4-break will be more powerful. }
5... Nf6 { The main move. } 6. O-O Qc7 { Stopping e5. } 7. Qe2 d6 8. c4
{ The most popular move. } 8... g6 9. Nc3 Bg7 10. Rd1 O-O
{ Black has a weakness on the d6-pawn, and Adams show in his games how to treat this kind of positions with White. }
11. Nf3 Nc6 12. h3
{ A useful move that takes away the g4 square from Black's pieces. } 12... b6
13. Bg5 { 13.Bf4  is not bad either. } 13... Bb7 14. Rac1 Ne5 15. Nxe5 dxe5 16.
b4
{ Black's structure is not ideal -unless the knight gets to d4, which is far away from now. White is better, as he has good play on the queenside. }
