[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6
{ This move introduces the Paulsen, a very flexible system in which Black keeps his options open.   Most of the time Black will keep the d7-pawn there for a while, which makes it difficult for White to castle queenside because, against any Nc3-Be3 system, Black will go ...Bb4 and carry out the ...d5 break.   On the other side of the coin, White is usually better developed than Black in these lines, which increases the possibility of the first player gaining an advantage. }
5. Bd3
{ The idea of this move is to prevent Black from playing b4. The reason is that the a4-break will be more powerful. }
5... Nf6 { The main move. } 6. O-O Qc7 { Stopping e5. } 7. Qe2 d6 8. c4
{ The most popular move. } 8... Nbd7 9. b3
{ This move stops ...Ne5, as now the c4-pawn is protected. The downside is that it weakens the c3-square and the b5-break from Black can be sometimes annoying. }
9... g6 10. Nc3 Bg7 11. Rd1 O-O 12. Bb2 { The bishop is not doing much here. }
12... b6 13. Rac1 Bb7 { Black is fine here. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Lesson 35: 2.Nf3 e6 - Paulsen"]
[Black "Paulsen 5.Bd3 Nf6 #23"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6
{ This move introduces the Paulsen, a very flexible system in which Black keeps his options open.   Most of the time Black will keep the d7-pawn there for a while, which makes it difficult for White to castle queenside because, against any Nc3-Be3 system, Black will go ...Bb4 and carry out the ...d5 break.   On the other side of the coin, White is usually better developed than Black in these lines, which increases the possibility of the first player gaining an advantage. }
5. Bd3
{ The idea of this move is to prevent Black from playing b4. The reason is that the a4-break will be more powerful. }
5... Nf6 { The main move. } 6. O-O Qc7 { Stopping e5. } 7. Qe2 d6 8. c4
{ The most popular move. } 8... Nbd7 9. Nf3 Be7
{ The bishop goes to e7 here because White has commited the knight to f3 and, therefore, he cannot play the typical dangerous plan f4, Kh1, Nc3, Bd2 Re1, e5. }
10. Nc3 b6
{ Black can now go for a Hedgehog structure, and this guarantees a nice position. THe dark-squared bshop is better on e7 than on g7 here, as it keeps the d6-pawn protected. }
