{ Black has some initiative. } 14. Bg5 Re8
{ Kasparov won this game in absolutely brilliant style and it's one of the best chess games that was ever played:   15.Qd2  b5  16.Rad1  Nd3  17.Nab1  h6  18.Bh4  b4  19.Na4  Bd6  20.Bg3  Rc8  21.b3  g5  22.Bxd6  Qxd6  23.g3  Nd7  24.Bg2  Qf6  25.a3  a5  26.axb4  axb4  27.Qa2  Bg6  28.d6  g4  29.Qd2  Kg7  30.f3  Qxd6  31.fxg4  Qd4+  32.Kh1  Nf6  33.Rf4  Ne4  34.Qxd3  Nf2+  35.Rxf2  Bxd3  36.Rfd2  Qe3  37.Rxd3  Rc1  38.Nb2  Qf2  39.Nd2  Rxd1+  40.Nxd1  Re1+  0-1, Karpov @@StartBracket@@2720@@EndBracket@@ - Kasparov @@StartBracket@@2700@@EndBracket@@, Moscow 1985. }
