{ 5...Bc5 is a surprise weapon but frankly speaking, I don't even know what Black is hoping for. }
6. Ndb5 { 6.Ndb5  Bb4  7.Qg4  is unnecessarily complicated. } 6... Nf6
{ 6...d6?  7.Bf4  e5  8.Be3  wins the d-pawn.   White has two ways to get an advantage now: }
7. Nd6+ { I prefer 7.Nd6+ over 7.Bf4. } 7... Ke7 8. Bf4 e5 9. Nf5+ Kf8 10. Bg5
d6 11. Bc4
{ I find this solution more convincing than 7.Bf4. Black's king is on f8 and the d5-square is weak. }
