6. Be3 Nf6 { 6...Qc7  7.Qd2  transposes to the Taimanov. } 7. Qd2
{ The critical move. } 7... e5
{ If Black wants to avoid transposing to a Taimanov system, the tactical solution 7...e5 could serve him well. }
8. Nf5 d5 9. exd5 Nb4
{ 9...Nb4 was played almost exclusively here, but  9...Bxf5  10.dxc6  Qc7  could also work - according to the engines, Black is close to equalizing. }
10. g4
{ The engines like White's position here but this position hasn't been reached in practice yet. The alternative  10.Ng3  is not so critical. }
