6. Be2
{ The second main move after  6.Be3  and formerly the main system. Together with  6.g3  it is White's positional approach, as opposed to the sharper  6.Be3  . Black needs to study it well but should equalize. }
6... a6 7. O-O Nf6 8. Be3 { The most principle move. } 8... Be7
{ Going for the Scheveningen is best and is doing fine, according to modern theory. The alternatives are flawed. }
9. f4 d6
{ I'd advise Black players to play like this, but keep in mind it requires a lot of study. White has two main approaches. He would love to get both a4 and Qg3, but that's simply not possible. Therefore, he has to choose. }
