{ All in all, @@StartFEN@@r1b1kbnr/ppqp1ppp/2n1p3/8/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Be2  is a very reliable variation for White. especially because Taimanov players tend to be reluctant to play ...d6 and switch to a Scheveningen.However, we have seen that alternatives such as  @@StartFEN@@r1b1kb1r/1pqp1ppp/p1n1pn2/8/3NP3/2N1B3/PPP1BPPP/R2Q1RK1 b kq - 3 8@@EndFEN@@  8...Bb4  are pleasant for White. Actually, White is being cornered in this Scheveningen system and Black players don't need to study a big pile of theory to get a good game. Just keep in mind the ...Nxd4 followed by ...e5 ideas.For White, the  @@StartFEN@@r1b1kbnr/ppqp1ppp/2n1p3/8/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6.g3  system seems worth checking and adding to your repertoire together with  6.Be2  . Even the rare  6.Qd3  could come in handy. Anyway,  6.Be3  is the main move and the most reliable weapon against the Taimanov. }
