{ This lesson will be entirely devoted to Taimanov with  6.Be3  , the most dangerous line for Black and the most played at the grandmaster level. }
6... Nf6 { It is almost refuted nowadays. } 7. f4
{ After this move, trouble begins for Black. } 7... Qb6
{ Doesn't work tactically. } 8. e5 Ng4 9. Bg1 Qxb2 10. Ndb5
{ 10.Ncb5  is also winning, after  11...Bb4+  12.Ke2  Black's position is just bad. }
10... Bb4 11. Kd2 { White is clearly better. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
