{ This lesson will be entirely devoted to Taimanov with  6.Be3  , the most dangerous line for Black and the most played at the grandmaster level. }
6... a6 7. g4
{ It seems strange to play g4 when the opponent's knight is still not on f6, and what is more, Black has not played d6, so he could exploit the weakness of the dark squares. But, even if my impression is not good, what matters is the engines' assessment, which confirm this is a very dangerous move for Black. }
7... b5 { The most popular move. } 8. Nxc6 Qxc6
