{ This lesson will be entirely devoted to Taimanov with  6.Be3  , the most dangerous line for Black and the most played at the grandmaster level. }
6... a6 7. Qd2 { The old main line. } 7... Nf6 8. f4
{ It is a serious option that I would advise you to play and analyze thoroughly. }
8... b5 9. e5 b4 10. Ncb5
{ A typical maneuver in several Sicilian lines, when the queen is on c7, White attacks the f6 knight and Black responds by counterattacking the one on b4. }
10... axb5 11. Nxb5 Qb8 12. exf6 gxf6 13. a4
{ Anand played  13.c4  in his game against Harikrishna, Munich 2015, but I think a4 it's stronger. }
13... bxa3 14. bxa3
{ A very difficult position to evaluate. According to the ingine, White is slightly better probably thanks to the strong knight in b5, which compensates for the spoiled structure. }
