1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be3
{ This lesson will be entirely devoted to Taimanov with  6.Be3  , the most dangerous line for Black and the most played at the grandmaster level. }
6... a6 7. Qf3
{ The most dangerous move. Black has yet to prove that he can equalize against Qf3. We analyzed  7.a3  via the a3 move order.  7.Be2  is a transposition to the 6. Be2 system, which we covered in the previous lesson. }
7... Nf6 8. O-O-O Ne5
{ Again,  8...Bb4  isn't good.  9.Nxc6  bxc6  10.Bd4  , and if  10...e5  then  11.Qg3  and White is just better.   Black can also plays in Scheveningen-style, with  8...Be7  9.Kb1  d6  but after  10.Nxc6  things look bad for Black;  10...bxc6  11.g4  Rb8  12.g5  Nd7  13.h4  and, according to engines. Black is close to lost.   Also  8...Nxd4  9.Bxd4  e5  10.Qg3  d6  11.Be3  isn't enough for Black to equalize. }
9. Qg3 b5
{ The main position of the variation.  9...h5  now doesn't work, after  10.f4  Neg4  11.e5  White is just better. }
10. a3
{ A relatively new move, played twice by Vachier-Lagrave in the Bundesliga, in 2018 with Anand, and in 2019 with Harikrishna. In both games, White won. It seems crazy because both ...b4 and ....Bxa3 seems extremely dangerous, but Black has nothing better than ...Bb7. }
10... Bb7 11. Bxb5
{ And the game becomes very tactical. Perhaps with extremely precise play Black holds, but it is by no means simple. }
11... Rc8
{ After  11...Bxa3  12.Bf4  is very strong. And if @@StartFEN@@r3kb1r/1bqp1ppp/p3pn2/1B2n3/3NP3/P1N1B1Q1/1PP2PPP/2KR3R b kq - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11...axb5  12.Ndxb5  Qb8  13.Bb6  is also very good for White. }
12. Ba4
{ A line that only engines could have discovered. A risk-avoiding human eye looking at the position immediately notices Black's threats at a3 and c3. }
12... Nxe4
{ If  12...Bxa3  , after the cold-blooded  13.Nde2  White is better. } 13. Nxe4
{ The main move, introducing a long forced line. } 13... Bxe4 14. Bf4 Qa5 15.
Bxe5 Qxa4 16. Rd2
{ With sharp play in the game Vachier-Lagrave-Harikrishna, Solingen 2019. } *

