{ Even though I studied and played a lot of these Nxc6 variations for White, I was often not happy to play with the king on e2 as Black has a lot of tricks. Maybe in the future a method for obtaining a clear advantage will be discovered, but until then the practical benefits are in Black's favor. However, it's very direct play and needs to be taken seriously for both sides.   I expect to see a number of games both at club level and at the top level to continue the discussion about the validity of this variation for Black, but right now it is passing scrutiny. }
