7... a6 8. Na3 b5
{ Obviously the best move in the position, White wants to get the knight closer to the d5-square, this move prevents that plan and threatens ...b4 as well. }
9. Nd5
{ So today we are going to study this move, 9.Nd5, a kind of positional system. It has been played countless times on the top level.  Now Black has to be very accurate, after listening to this course you will have good knowledge of the nuances of this system and if your opponent is not so well-prepared then you have considerable chances to get a certain advantage out of the opening. }
9... Be7
{ The only move to fight for equality, and even if Black most often equalizes on the top level, just one wrong move and White will get a significant advantage. Definitely, a rather risk-free variation for White if you know what you are doing.  For those of you who want to play this line with Black, I'll try to give a detailed analysis of the current state of theory, the best directions and certain concrete variations - that will already be enough information for you to play it with Black @@StartBracket@@if you are not in the top 10 of the world@@EndBracket@@.   9...Be6  is a mistake, you'll understand this more after watching the next lesson.  10.Bxf6  gxf6  11.c3  f5  12.exf5  Bxf5  and Black simply lost a tempo. }
10. Nxe7 { This move is harmless. } 10... Qxe7
{ Even this move is doing very well and I can show you briefly the ideas. } 11.
c4 { The only way White can really challenge Black. } 11... Nd4
{ Not the only move but the most direct one.   11...O-O  12.cxb5  Nd4  and Black manages to equalize thanks to the usual Sveshnikov counterplay. }
12. cxb5
{ The most challenging, now Black can equalize in two different ways. } 12...
O-O
{ I also discovered that this move is doing perfectly fine for Black, threatening ...Qb7. }
13. Nc2 Ne6 14. Bxf6 Qxf6 15. bxa6 Qh4
{ A very important move. It is very uncomfortable for White to defend the e4-pawn. Although the position is equal according to the engines, practically this position is much easier and more interesting from the Black perspective. }
16. Bd3 Nf4 { ...Nf4 is fine here and Black is doing great. } *

