13. g3 { The main idea in this line. } 13... Bg5
{ A logical move, trying to put the bishop on h6. } 14. h4 Bh6 15. Bh3
{ The main idea behind h3.   With the queen on d1,  15.g4  is not dangerous anymore. After  15...Bf4  ,  Black gets his bishop to safety and White is definitely not interested in giving up his monster knight for the f4-bishop. Black is doing fine. }
15... Be6
{ White's point is that this move doesn't work for tactical reasons. } 16. Bxe6
fxe6 17. Qh5+
{ Although the engine only gives a slight edge for White after  17...Kf8  , from a practical point of view, it is unpleasant for Black to play with a king in the center. }
