{ Probably the best move. Now there is not direct tactics but we have a very strong move now. }
19... Be7 { A very unpleasant resource. Black is threatening d5. } 20. a3 Rf3
{ Another thematic Sveshnikov maneuver, Black is organizing his counterplay from all sides of the board.  More so now the white king can't even castle now because the g3 pawn is hanging. All in all, I believe this is almost a refutation for the g3-g4-Bh3 idea, I really don't see how White can fight for any opening advantage in this line. When the players finally realized that, they started playing Bg2 instead. }
