{ 14...Bd7 is not popular at all and honestly looks a bit strange@@StartBracket@@the bishop on e6 looks better placed@@EndBracket@@ but it might be an interesting move. }
15. Bd3 { The main move by far. } 15... f5
{ And here during the 1990s I had a lot of games in this position, it wasn't easy at the time but nowadays it is clear that Black is more or less fine in this position. }
16. Qh5 e4 17. Bc2 Ne7
{ I played two or three games here with Black and there were small issues here and there but with the help of modern engines I can be sure that this is safe for Black. }
18. Bb3 { This is another possible move here. } 18... Ng6 19. g3 Kh8
{ Very sharp position, White has to be very careful. } 20. Nf4 Nxf4 21. gxf4
{ Again, more or less a dynamically equal position. } *

