11. c4
{ Also not a good move but was played by Hikaru Nakamura in a classical game long time ago against Boris Gelfand. }
11... Qa5+
{ This move is much stronger, it probably even is slightly better for Black. Gelfand played 11...b4 which is also perfectly fine. }
12. Qd2 Qxd2+ 13. Kxd2 Bh6+ 14. Kd1 fxe4
{ Many moves are fine for Black, including  14...Kf8  . } 15. cxb5 Nd4 16. Nc7+
Ke7 17. Nxa8 Bg4+ 18. Ke1 Rxa8 19. bxa6 d5
{ A very forced line.  Black is a lot more active with a nice center, two powerful bishops and a strong knight on d4. Black is probably slightly better here according to the engines, in a practical game I don't think this is playable. }
