{ This is an interesting move that is currently out of fashion, Black needs to be accurate after this move. Since I don't see any advantage anyway in other lines, this is a nice weapon to throw at your opponent. }
11... fxe4 12. Bg2 Bg7 { The best move. } 13. Bxe4 Be6 14. Qh5
{ This is how White manages to stop castling. } 14... Rc8 15. c3 Ne7 16. Rd1
Rc5 17. Nxe7 Qxe7 18. Nc2
{ Threatening Ne3 with a strategically winning position. } 18... d5
{ Just in time. } 19. Bf5
{ Now  19...d4  is the simplest to make a draw. This variation is very well-known and it really puts Black to the test. I don't understand why this is out of fashion as White is risking very little. }
*

