{ The game MVL-Carlsen went like this. White is better here, although Vachier-Lagrave lost in the end. }
13. Rd1 Qc8 14. Qf3 h6 15. Bc1
{ White has an active rook on d1 and a better pawn structure. On the other hand, Black will try to castle by hand by playing ...g6 and ...Bg7. In conclusion, the position is playable for both sides. }
