{ This move is played from time to time. Even Carlsen tried it in a rapid game against Vachier-Lagrave. However, Black doesn't equalize after this move. Let's see how the game can continue. }
6. Bg5
{ 6.Bc4  is also an option that gives White a slight advantage compared to the main Najdorf or Dragon main lines.   After  6.f3  e5  7.Nb3  Be7  8.Be3  O-O  9.Qd2  a5  , Black has typical Najdorf play and his point is that he didn't waste a tempo on ...a6.  10.a4  Na6  . This position is quite playable for Black. }
