[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Lesson 46: Classical Sicilian - Rauzer"]
[Black "Classical Sicilian - Rauzer - Main Line 9.f4 h6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5
{ The Rauzer is, by far, the main system against the Classical Sicilian. Best by test! Black has to work to equalize, even though some positions are not so clear. I'd say White is always better and I'd recommend  6.Bg5  .We'll see the current state of theory and some new ideas and possible directions for both sides, and I'll tell you which lines could be recommended for Black players. }
6... Bd7
{ Lately, this move order has been employed to reach the main lines, when in the past the usual order was  6...e6  7.Qd2  a6  8.O-O-O  Bd7  . One point could be to avoid sidelines like  @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pp2pppp/2np1n2/6B1/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 4 6@@EndFEN@@  6...e6  7.Qd3  . }
7. Qd2
{ Here,  7.Qd3  is met by  7...Rc8  and  8.O-O-O  doesn't work so well due to  8...Qa5  threatening ...Nb4 and forcing  9.Bxf6  gxf6=  .A better try is  @@StartFEN@@2rqkb1r/pp1bpppp/2np1n2/6B1/3NP3/2NQ4/PPP2PPP/R3KB1R w KQk - 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Nb3  a6  9.O-O-O  e6  but nothing that should worry Black.   Anyway, asseen under the traditional move order, I believe Black is fine after  7.Qd3  e6  . }
7... a6
{ The only sensible approach, in my opinion, is ...a6 and ...e6. Remember that  7...e6?  is just bad due to  8.Ndb5  . }
8. O-O-O
{ Now  8.Bxf6  gxf6  9.O-O-O  is not the same, as Black hasn't played ...h6 and that changes everything. Not only that saves a tempo, but ...Bh6 is possible in some lines. Both  9...Rc8  or  9...Nxd4  10.Qxd4  Rc8  are fine.   8.f4  e6  transposes to main lines because White has nothing better than  9.O-O-O  . }
8... e6
{ Of course, the most usual move order to reach this position is @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pp2pppp/2np1n2/6B1/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 4 6@@EndFEN@@  6...e6  7.Qd2  a6  8.O-O-O  Bd7  . Here White has two main setups. }
9. f4
{ This may be more dangerous and ambitious, but it also allows Black more counterplay. Many lines are rather direct and complicated. }
9... h6 { This is not advisable. } 10. Bh4
{ The point is that  10...Nxe4  is not winning a pawn after  11.Qe1  Nf6  12.Nf5!  Qa5  Forced.  13.Nxd6+  Bxd6  14.Rxd6  O-O-O  . White has two bishops and is better. Black has reasonable drawing chances but this is not what Sicilian players are aiming for. }
10... g5
{ This system was very popular and well considered. Even Kasparov played it. However, it has fallen out of fashion and I don't believe in it.  10...Be7  11.Nf3  b5  is a bad version ofthe main lines: the inclusion of ...h6 Bh4 makes  12.e5  work here. Black should try  @@StartFEN@@r2qk2r/1p1bbpp1/p1nppn1p/8/4PP1B/2N2N2/PPPQ2PP/2KR1B1R b kq - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11...Qc7  but it is unpleasant.  12.Kb1  Rd8  13.Bd3  b5  14.g4  and White is faster. }
11. fxg5 Ng4 12. Nxc6 Bxc6 13. Kb1 { Black's position strikes me as bad. }
13... Ne5
{ 13...Be7  is no better.  14.Qd4  and now  14...Rf8  , with a big advantage for White, it's Black's best because after  14...Ne5  15.Bg3  Black has no good reply. }
14. Qe3 { The most precise. } 14... Ng6
{ After  14...Be7  15.Bg3  Bxg5  16.Qf2  Black has coordination issues and his king lacks a clear destination. Short castle seems out of the question and a future long castle may run into Qa7 ideas. }
15. Bg3 Qxg5 { Black got the pawn back but has a lot of issues to address. }
16. Qe1
{ I couldn't find anything decent for Black. Here is a possible continuation. }
16... O-O-O
{ In case of  16...Ne5  White can just play positionally:  17.Be2  Be7  18.Rf1  hitting the f7-pawn and thus stopping long castle. }
17. h4 Qa5 18. Rh3 { The rook enters the game. } 18... Ne5 19. a3
{ A quiet suggestion from the engine. } 19... Rg8 20. Bf4 Bg7 21. Be2
{ To a human eye, Black's position doesn't look that bad, but engines claim a big advantage and I couldn't find a way to equalize. The h6-pawn is weak and Black lacks counterplay. My conclusion is that @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/1p1b1ppp/p1nppn2/6B1/3NPP2/2N5/PPPQ2PP/2KR1B1R b kq f3 0 9@@EndFEN@@  9...h6  is not an option for Black. }
