[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Qf3
{ 6.Qf3 is by far the worst move of White's 6th-move sidelines. The problem is that White needs h2-h3 if he wants to castle queenside, to prevent ...Bg4. }
6... g6 7. h3 { 7.Be3  Bg7  8.h3  transposes to the text move. } 7... Bg7 8.
Be3 O-O 9. O-O-O Nc6 10. g4
{ Playing g4 makes sense, using the fact that h3 is already played. } 10... Bd7
{ The queen is simply misplaced on f3 and the e4-pawn is vulnerable to the typical ...Rc8-xc3 sacrifice. }
