[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Lesson 47: Najdorf - 6th Move Sidelines"]
[Black "Najdorf - 6.f4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f4 e5
{ 6...Nbd7  7.Be2  g6  is quite complicated but after 6...e5, I don't see the slightest problem for Black. }
7. Nb3 { This is more interesting from White's perspective. } 7... Nbd7 8. g4
{ The more classical approach  8.a4  Be7  9.Be2  O-O  10.O-O  b6  11.Bf3  Bb7  shouldn't frighten Black. }
8... d5 9. exd5 Nb6 10. fxe5 Nfxd5
{ White doesn't have an advantage but the position is fresh and more importantly, it's a game. }
