1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f4 e5
{ 6...Nbd7  7.Be2  g6  is quite complicated but after 6...e5, I don't see the slightest problem for Black. }
7. Nb3 { This is more interesting from White's perspective. } 7... Nc6
{ I prefer 7...Nc6 over 7...Nbd7. } 8. f5 { 8.Be2  Be7  9.O-O  O-O= } 8... Be7
{ 8...d5  might also work. } 9. g4 h6 10. Be3 b5
{ The e4-pawn will always be weak in this structure and it's very easy to get worse with White. }
