{ This is an interesting move for White and it has been played by Carlsen, Firouzja, Anand, Giri and other top players. White is always in full control and Black must be accurate to equalize. }
6... e5
{ 6...e6  7.Be2  transposes to the Classical Scheveningen system @@StartBracket@@with O-O for White@@EndBracket@@, which is a respected system and more importantly, not all Najdorf players are willing or able to play the Scheveningen with Black. }
7. Nf3 Be7 8. Bg5 Be6
{ As we have seen before, Black wants to play ...Nbd7 and ...h6 so that he can recapture on f6 with the knight. In other words, ...Be6 practically forces White to take on f6.   After  8...Nbd7  9.Bc4  , the bishop is strong on the a2-g8 diagonal and White has some plus. }
