12. a5
{ White is running out of useful moves.  12.h3  a useful waiting move is met by another useful waiting move...  12...h6  13.Be3  Nbd7  and now the e3 square is not free, and this Nd2 maneuver is no longer so dangerous. }
12... Nbd7
{ Now we finally develop the knight after White has locked the queenside structure. The idea is to push ...b5 when we can recapture with our knight. }
13. h3
{ 13.Nd2  b5  gives Black quick counterplay.  14.axb6  Nxb6  with ...Nc4 ideas. }
13... h6 14. Be3 b5 { Creating counterplay. } 15. axb6 Nxb6 16. Na5 Nc4
{ Not the only move, but a simple option, exchanging the knights and maintaining pressure on the queenside. Black is fine. }
