8. h4
{ This was played, strangely enough, by Wesley So who is a positional player. }
8... Be6
{ Naturaly development.  8...h5  is playable, but weakens the g5 square. after  9.Bg5  Be6  the position is playable but better to stay solid. }
9. f4 exf4
{ Now even though it allows White's bishop out in one move, we can get away with this because White has spent a move weakening the g4 square, and h4 is a weakness. }
10. Bxf4 Nc6 11. Qd2 d5 { The positionally desireable break. } 12. exd5 Nxd5
{ This should equalize for Black. There's no realistic attack with h4-h5. } *

