{ Bringing more forces to the queenside and bearing down the c-file, typical Sicilian play.  12...Bd8  13.Qd2  Bb6  is also logical. }
13. Qd2 { Gives Black time to carry out the bishop maneuver. } 13... Bd8
{ Following through with our idea of activating the bishop. } 14. Red1 Rc6
{ Defending laterally, just in time. } 15. Nd5 Bxd5
{ We simply take even though the knight probably isn't threatening much. } 16.
exd5 Rc4
{ Play has clearly shifted to the queenside, giving the Najdorf player what they want. }
