{ Waiting for Black to commit to ...Be6.  8.f4  can now be met by  8...b5  when f5 is not a threat. }
8... O-O { 8...Be6  is too early again in view of  9.f4  . } 9. Kh1
{ This was a very popular move in the middle to end of the 90's but now the engine laughs at White's attempts and say Black is fine everywhere, probably due to the extra tempo. }
9... b6
{ Not a bad move at all, but a strange idea. Black wants to provoke White into defending e4 in an unconventional way and only then proceed normally on the queenside. }
10. Be3 Bb7 11. f3 b5
{ Losing a tempo, effectively but ensuring you have ...b4 after a4. } 12. a4 b4
13. Nd5 Nxd5
{ There were some discussions a while back including between Anand-Gelfand. }
14. exd5 Nd7 15. c4 bxc3 16. bxc3 Bg5
{ Activating the bishop, when Black should have no problems at all after a trade. White might have some play on the queenside here but it should be ok for Black. }
*

