7... Nbd7
{ A very good system, and perhaps even simpler than  7...b5  . I tried to find a problem for Black in this line while preparing this lesson but to no avail. White has tried many moves in this position, but none is really dangerous. }
8. O-O Nc5
{ The knight has a nice post on c5 and can take the bishop on b3 at any moment. }
9. Re1 Be7 10. Bg5
{ There are many games that went like this, but I don't understand why would White consider that the positions could be any better. }
10... h6 11. Bh4 Nxb3
{ Black is fine in different ways, but this is how Maxime Vachier-Lagrave tackled this system. }
12. axb3 g5 13. Bg3 e5
{ This is maybe already unnecessary, and I would say that already after @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/1p3ppp/p2ppn2/2n5/3NP3/1BN5/PPP2PPP/R1BQR1K1 b kq - 5 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Be7  , Black doesn't need to know  more. ...Nxb3 can be inserted, equalizing the game. }
