9... Qxf6 10. Nd5 { Or first  10.Qd3  , which will lead to the same. } 10...
Qd8 { MVL played a million games here with Black and with very good results. }
11. Nec3 g6 12. Bc4 Bh6
{ We suddenly landed in some sort of Sveshnikov line and you can have a look at the games played by the top players. Black is doing well and I am also not a big fan of White's setup. The knight looks nice on d5, but White is also a bit stuck, as it is not easy to continue. }
13. Bb3
{ Black often places the king on f8 in this position or tries to play ...Nc6. }
13... Nc6 { Planning to plant a knight on d4. } *

