6... e6 { By far, the main move. } 7. f4
{ The main tabiya of the variation. Black has a lot of moves here, but some are dubious after being refuted by engines. I'd say  7...Nbd7  and  7...Be7  are the soundest and most human options, whereas  7...Qb6  is taken over by engines and there, memory weighs more than chess skills. }
7... Nbd7
{ The most popular line and something I would certainly recommend to Black players. The game is usually not so forcing and definitely more interesting, even though inevitably you will need to memorize some lines. Still, it's more human and more chess than other systems covered in this chapter. As usual,  8.Qd2  h6  is not how White plays in the 6.Bg5 Najdorf. }
