10. a3 { Prophylaxis against Black's standard ...b4 push. } 10... Bb7
{ Gelfand, a long-time Najdorf player, and expert, tried this sideline against me. }
11. g4 Rc8 12. Bxf6 gxf6
{ Unfortunately for him, I had come well-prepared. I think this is not enough to equalize due to the following maneuver. }
13. h4 Qb6 14. Rh3
{ The rook is very active on the third rank. I went on to win the game. } *

