12. Qd3 b5
{ After  12...Nd7  13.Qb3  , there is again an issue with the pawn  on e6. }
13. Nb6 Nxe3 14. Qxe3 Ra7 15. Nd5 { Otherwise, the knight gets trapped on b6. }
15... Rb7
{ The position is nominally better for White, but with accurate moves, Black can easily equalize fully and make a draw. }
