{ Instead of playing all the concrete lines, White has the option of going for slow, positional play. This won't yield a big advantage, of course, but it is always a good idea to play accurately as Black since this is the type of Sicilian that resembles Petroff. If you get a worse position, you will suffer for the rest of the game and defend passively. I would recommend this variation for White, at least from time to time since Black's task is not trivial. }
