{ I believe this should be okay for Black, as with the pawn on b5, Black has access to ...Qb7 followed by ...Nd7 @@StartBracket@@just watch out for Bxe6 and Ng5, to not lose the e6-pawn@@EndBracket@@. You can follow the games of MVL in the @@StartFEN@@rn1q1rk1/1p2bppp/p2pbn2/4p3/4P3/1BN1BN2/PPP2PPP/R2Q1RK1 b - - 7 10@@EndFEN@@  10...b5  variation to see how he equalizes. }
