{ Nakamura erred with  18.Qf2  , as he wanted to avoid  18.Qe3  Nc4  . } 18...
Rc6 19. f4 Rfc8
{ Black has a powerful initiative on the c-file and Gelfand won the game in great style against Nakamura, Paris FIDE GP, 2013:  20.Qg3  Nd7  21.Bxg7  Kxg7  22.f5  Rxc3  23.bxc3  Qxa3+  24.Kd2  Nf6  25.Qd3  Bc4  26.Qd4  d5  27.exd5  Bxd5  28.Rg1  Be4  29.Bd3  Qa5  30.Qb4  Qc7  31.Bxe4  a5  32.Qxb7  Qf4+  33.Ke2  Rc7  34.Qb6  Nxe4  35.Qd4+  Kh7  36.c4  Rd7  37.Qe3  Ng3+  38.Qxg3  Qxg3  39.Rxd7  Qe5+  0-1. }
