{ Let's start with  6.Be3  and see the theory where White is not playing f3, and then we  move on to  6.f3  , when we will discuss all the main lines. After both @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/1p2pppp/p2p1n2/8/3NP3/2N1B3/PPP2PPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6...e6  and  6...e5  , White has a number of interesting options, especially against  6...e6  , this system  without f3 could prove even more dangerous. }
6... Ng4
{ Nonetheless, Black also gets an additional option with this move, which was developed by Kasparov, and currently, Black is doing well in this line. White is unable to pose any serious problems and at the top level,  6...Ng4  is very annoying to face. Of course, it's not very easy to equalize either, White has a number of tries, but it is a very serious option for Black. }
7. Bg5
{ On a side note, I see often players who want to go for the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/1p2pppp/p2p1n2/8/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Be3  system, but when they have to deal with  6...Ng4  , often play  7.Bc1  here, and after  7...Nf6  , which is considered the best move, they switch back to  8.f3  positions or another system altogether. }
7... h6 8. Bh4 g5 9. Bg3 Bg7
{ Kasparov developed this system, where White tried many moves here. } 10. h3
Ne5 11. f3
{ Quite a popular continuation, with many games on the top level, but I don't really understand why as Black is very solid. }
11... Nbc6 12. Bf2 Be6
{ 12...Ng6  is also an option, but I like how Boris Gelfand played and won against both Karjakin and Nakamura. }
13. Qd2 { After  13.h4  Rc8  , Black has no problems either. } 13... Rc8
{ Of course, Black still has to be precise. } 14. O-O-O Nxd4 15. Bxd4
{ If only White could play more moves at once... The game is very concrete and Black is in time. }
15... Qa5 16. a3 O-O
{ A good decision, even though it may seem tricky with the pawn on g5, but Black is extremely active. }
17. h4 g4 18. Qe3 Nc4
{ Now  18...Rc6  19.f4  is not totally clear, but it could be in White's favor. }
19. Bxc4 Rxc4 20. Bxg7 Kxg7
{ Black's king is a bit weak, but the king on c1 is also under fire. } 21. f4
f6 22. Rd3 Rfc8
{ I am not sure who is mating whom, but I believe Black is totally fine. } *

