{ An odd-looking move, but a strong one, using the long diagonal. Also, after  11...e6  12.Ne3  Nbd7  13.Qd2  b5  14.f3  , the engines give a plus for White, but I am not sure if that is really the case in reality, as the position is very complicated. }
12. Nf5 Bxf5 13. exf5 Bxb2 { The game gets very sharp. } 14. Rb1 Qa5+ 15. Qd2
Qxa2 16. Rd1
{ White has initiative but is still underdeveloped and two pawns down in this extremely complicated position. The good news is: my engine is claiming that Black is doing all right! }
16... Nd4
{ Black is trying to play for a win, but  16...Bd4  can also be investigated and is good enough for a draw. }
17. c3 Qxd5 18. cxd4 Qa2
{ The final assessment of the engine is that Black is better, although that is hard to tell with a human eye. }
