{ A rather underestimated system, but Black can already play  9...h5  10.a3  Bb7  , reaching the position we will discuss later on. }
10. g4 { Or  10.a3  , which leads to the same. } 10... Nb6
{ This was Kasparov's idea. If  10...h6  instead, the position becomes problematic for Black after both  11.h4  and  11.a3  . }
11. g5 Nfd7 12. a3 Rc8
{ Kasparov played quite a few games like this and was, as always, successful. The engines give now a serious advantage for White, but not everything is that clear, especially from a practical point of view. For instance, when I was trying to play a few logical moves against the engine, to understand why would White have such a significant advantage, the evaluations started to drop. You can surely explore this line further. }
*

