{ A very principled move and I hope I am still making sense and that you are still able to follow, but since this system is pretty much about move orders, we have to try and digest them. }
9... b4
{ This position becomes fashionable now, as Black can no longer the ...h5 setups − it is very dangerous, but maybe holdable. }
10. Nce2
{ After  10.Na4  h6  , there is nothing better for White than  11.O-O-O  , reaching the same position as in Kramnik-Topalov, which is good for Black given the  11...Ne5  strong idea. }
10... h6 11. O-O-O
{ There is a big difference with the positions where the knight was on b8 and Balck could play ...e5, ...Nc6, ...d5, etc. Now, Black has to play only moves. }
