9. Be2 Nbd7
{ This remains the classical 6.Be2 systems against the Najdorf, but with the 'weird' move ...h5 included. In fact, ...h5 makes a lot of sense. }
10. a4 Be7 11. O-O Rc8 12. a5 h4 13. Qd2
{ So far, the moves have been logical and need no explanation. } 13... O-O
{ Engines like this move, although this move is also fine, strangely enough. The pawn on h4 is difficult to attack. }
14. Rfd1 { If  14.Bf2  Nh5  . } 14... Qc7 { Stopping Nd5. } 15. Rac1 Rfe8
{ With the possible idea of playing ...Nf8-Ng6 at some point. I'd feel happy if I had to play this position with Black: objetively, the position is slightly better for White, but in practice Black has great winning chances. }
*

