{ This is a very strong move. } 10... b4 11. Nd5 Bxd5 12. exd5 Nb6 13. Bg1
{ This move was found by strong engines. I don't know the difference between placing the bishop on f2 or g1; probably this move is justified after a long line. The idea is to defend the d5-pawn, which cannot be taken now by any of Black's knights. }
13... Be7 { 13...Nfxd5  14.a5  13...Nbxd5  14.g5 } 14. a5 Nbxd5 15. g5
{ Wins a piece. } *

