18. c4
{ The most principled move.  18.Bd3  has been tried, but after  18...g6  , the position is drawish. White has compensation for the pawn, but not more. }
18... Nf4 19. Bxf4 exf4 20. h4 Qa4 21. Bd3
{ In case of  21.b3  Qb4  , Black is in time to organize counterplay on tghe queenside. }
21... bxc4 22. Qe4 g6 23. Bc2 Qe8
{ The correct move! This leads to a drawish position. White's setup feels nice, but Black holds everywhere. Vachier-Lagrave played the more natural  23...Qd7  , which turns out to be a mistake after  24.h5  and White was much better. }
